Title: Everyday Inspiration by Field Notes x Bellroy
Body (HTML):
Be ready to collect a thought, capture an idea, or jot down a note with this Field Notes and Bellroy collaboration. The Everyday Inspiration offers everything you need in one cleverly-crafted kit. Thoughtfully designed and carefully constructed, this is one companion you’ll want with you all the time.

Since we launched Field Notes, we’ve been keeping an eye on other brands doing interesting things. When Bellroy appeared in 2010, we had a feeling that their approach fit with ours: making products with love, sweating the details, and especially, talking about their business in an open, honest way. Eventually, we got together with the Bellroy crew and over a few beers at our Chicago HQ, we decided we had to do something together.

This is it.

A beautifully crafted, super-compact leather cover, precisely fitted to our Memo Books, The Everyday Inspiration is a perfect companion. The leather is vegetable tanned and dyed through to a rich charcoal color that will age gracefully. There’s room for business cards, receipts or tickets and you can clip your favorite pen to the spine. The Everyday Inspiration snaps closed to hold everything together with a sweet, magnetic click, and it fits easily in your back pocket.
Tags: back pocket, Bellroy, BREVILLE, business cards, collab, leather cover, pen clip, receipts, tickets

Title: Front Page by Field Notes
Body (HTML):
For years, people had been asking us to make a Reporter’s Notebook. So we did. Our Summer 2016 “Byline” Limited Edition was apparently exactly what people had hoped for. It was an instant classic, and quickly sold out. Then even more people wrote to ask us to make more Reporter’s Notebooks. So we did. “Front Page” is here, and will remain in production and in stock indefinitely.

So what’s changed? Only some cosmetic details. The cover is the same heavy 120#DTC Neenah stock, but in a lighter “Concrete” gray. The innards are the same Cougar 70# text paper, but bright white college-ruled with light gray lines. The Double-O-Binding is black rather than silver. That’s all, really.
